Package controls.nist

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Control
    The Control class is the data provided from NIST SP 800-53 and 800-53a.
    ControlAssessmentParser
    The Control Assessment Parser extracts the data from the NIST SP 800-53a Revision 4 and then populates the controls with the data.
    ControlEnhancement
    The Control Assessment from the NIST SP 800-53 and 800-53a Revision 4.
    ControlNumberSorter
    Sorts controls based on the control number.
    ControlParser
    The Control Parser extracts the data from the NIST SP 800-53 Revision 4 and then populates the controls with the data.
    NISTElementFactory
    The NIST Element Factory creates the Magic Draw classes from the NIST SP 800-53 and 800-53a Revision 4 standards data classes.
    Objective
    The Objective class is the data provided from NIST SP 800-53 and 800-53a.
    PotentialAssessment
    The Potential Assessment class is the data provided from NIST SP 800-53 and 800-53a.
    Reference
    The Reference class is the data provided from NIST SP 800-53 and 800-53a.
    SecurityRequirement
    The security requirement holds the requirement information from the NIST standard.
    SecurityRequirementParser
    The Control Parser extracts the data from the NIST SP 800-53 Revision 4 and then populates the controls with the data.
    Statement
    The Reference class is the data provided from NIST SP 800-53 and 800-53a.
    SupplementalGuidance
    The Supplemental Guidance class is the data provided from NIST SP 800-53.
    Withdrawn
    The Withdrawn class is the data provided from NIST SP 800-53 and 800-53a.
